  "question_text": "<h3>Top K Frequent Words</h3><p>Find $k$ most frequent words sorted by frequency and then dictionary order.</p>",
  "difficulty": "MEDIUM",
  "marks": 10,
  "input_format": "Array of strings, $k$.",
  "output_format": "Array of $k$ strings.",
  "constraints": [
    "n <= 500",
    "k <= n"
  ],
  "explanation": "Use a hash map for counts, then sort by $(-count, word)$ and take top $k$.",
  "answer": "def topKFrequent(words, k):\n    counts = collections.Counter(words)\n    return sorted(counts.keys(), key=lambda w: (-counts[w], w))[:k]",
